To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Hello can I please get all records for PBSO Caso No.  21-131644 and also the contact information for a "Detective Lee" who I was told was assigned to this case

There should not be any fees associated pertaining to this request, I would prefer the request be filled electronically, by e-mail attachment and/or download link as per Sunshine Law.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Mason C. turner

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

File number 173-HQ-6135 records on the theologian and minister Cecil Leonard Murray (September 26, 1929 – April 5, 2024).

His death is widely-known and widely reported; as such, privacy concerns under FOIA Exemptions 6 and 7 are voided, as are any concerns under the Privacy Act. For example, you may find his New York Times obituary at the following link: https://www.nytimes.com/2024/04/09/us/rev-cecil-murray-dead.html

In response to a FOIA request for FBI records on Murray, the FBI wrote to me on April 24, 2024 that “Records potentially responsive to your request were transferred to the National Archives and
Records Administration.” The letter referred to file number 173-HQ-6135. You may find the letter attached below.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Matthew Petti
